<TITLE> Police press charges against eight RU teachers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com)  Twenty people, including eight Rajshahi University teachers, have been accused in two separate cases of breaching emergency powers rules during the recent student protests. Following the student protests at Dhaka University, clashes erupted on Rajshahi University campus which resulted in the fatal shooting of a rickshaw driver by police on Aug 22. Metropolitan magistrate's court inspector Mahbubul Quddus Siddiqui told bdnews24.com that the chargesheets were submitted Saturday. Motihar police sub-inspector Faruk Hosssain filed one of the cases citing vandalism, while DGFI assistant director Shawkat Ali filed the second case on charges of setting a DGFI vehicle ablaze. Charges of vandalism have been brought against former RU vice chancellor Prof Saidur Rahman Khanalso a member of the Awami League's council of advisersconvener of RU's Progressive Teachers Community Prof Abdus Sobhan and associate professor of the management department Moloy Kumar Bhowmik. Associate professors Dulal Chandra Biswas and Selim Reza Newton, and assistant professor Abdullah Al Mamun of the mass communication and journalism department have also been included in the chargesheet, according to the investigation officer SI Nasir Uddin. Nasir Uddin told bdnews24.com: "The named individuals are accused of instigating unrest in violation of the emergency powers rules." The investigating officer in the DGFI vehicle arson case, Motihar police station's SI Mukter Hossain, said: "The accused in this case include professor Golam Sabbir Sattar Tapu from Rajshahi University's department of geology and mining and professor Sarwar Zahan Sajal and 12 others." Among the others accused are RU's deputy chief information officer Sadikul Islam, RU's Chhatra League general secretary Ayen Uddin and RU's former Chhatra Dal organising secretary Anwar Hossain Ujjal. "The accused have been charged with violating the emergency powers rules by instigating the burning of a car," he said. Joint forces detained Saidur Rahman Khan, Abdus Sobhan and Moloy Kumar Bhowmik following the student agitation at RU. On August 25 the police remanded them for 10 days. The court, however, sent them to jail Saturdayon the eighth day of their remandwhere they were rushed to the jail hospital after they fell sick. The police also arrested Sadikul Islam, the university's public relations officer from the campus on Aug 29. bdnews24.com/c
